HEADWORD: Olivine
<hw>Ol"i*vine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>olivine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A common name of the
yellowish green mineral chrysolite, esp. the variety found in eruptive
rocks. It is a silicate of magnesium and iron
(<chform>(Mg,Fe)SiO4</chform>).</def>⟦br⟧
